{"title_page": "MacGyver (2016 TV series)", "text_new": "{{about|the 2016 remake|the original show|MacGyver (1985 TV series)}}\n{{For|the current season|MacGyver (2016 TV series, season 4)}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = MacGyver\n| image = MacGyver Season 2 Title Card.png\n| caption = Title card starting with the second season\n| genre = [[Action-adventure fiction|Action-adventure]]\n| creator =\n| developer = [[Peter M. Lenkov]]\n| based_on = {{based on|''[[MacGyver (1985 TV series)|MacGyver]]''|[[Lee David Zlotoff]]}}\n| starring = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Lucas Till]]\n* [[George Eads]]\n* [[Sandrine Holt]]\n* [[Tristin Mays]]\n* [[Justin Hires]]\n* [[Meredith Eaton]]\n* [[Isabel Lucas]]\n* [[Levy Tran]]\n* [[Henry Ian Cusick]]\n}}\n| theme_music_composer = [[Randy Edelman]]\n| opentheme=\n| endtheme =\n| composer = Keith Power\n| country = United States\n| language = English\n| num_seasons = 4\n| num_episodes = 75\n| list_episodes = List of MacGyver (2016 TV series) episodes\n| executive_producer = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Henry Winkler]]\n* [[Paul Downs Colaizzo]]\n* [[James Wan]]\n* Lee David Zlotoff\n* Brett Mahoney\n* Michael Clear\n* Craig O'Neil\n}}\n| producer = {{Plainlist|\n*P. Todd Coe\n*Peter M. Tassler\n*Lucas Till (2020-)\n}}\n| location = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Marietta, Georgia]]\n*[[Los Angeles]], [[California]] (pilot)\n}}\n| cinematography = {{Plainlist|\n* Gabriel Beristain\n* James L. Carter\n* [[Peter Levy (cinematographer)|Peter Levy]]\n* Michael Martinez\n* Darren Genet\n* Christopher Duddy\n* Matthew Moriarty\n}}\n| editor = Mark Manos\n| camera =\n| runtime = 43 minutes\n| company = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Peter M. Lenkov|101st Street Entertainment]]\n* [[Atomic Monster Productions]]\n* [[Lionsgate Television]]\n* [[CBS Television Studios]]\n}}\n| distributor = [[CBS Television Distribution]]\n| network = [[CBS]]\n| picture_format = [[1080i]] ([[High Definition Television|HDTV]])\n| audio_format =\n| first_aired = {{Start date|2016|9|23}}\n| last_aired = {{End date|present}}\n| related = ''[[MacGyver (1985 TV series)|MacGyver]]'' (1985)\n| website = http://www.cbs.com/shows/macgyver/\n| production_website =\n}}\n\n'''''MacGyver''''' is an American [[Action-adventure fiction|action-adventure]] television series developed by [[Peter M. Lenkov]] and starring [[Lucas Till]] as [[MacGyver|the title character]]. It is a [[Reboot (fiction)|reboot]] of the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] [[MacGyver (1985 TV series)|series of the same name]] created by [[Lee David Zlotoff]], which aired from 1985 to 1992. The series premiered on September 23, 2016, on [[CBS]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/06/cbs-fall-premiere-dates-2016-1201776569/|title=CBS Sets Fall 2016 Premiere Dates, Slates JonBenet Ramsey Limited Series|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=June 21, 2016|accessdate=July 30, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2018, CBS renewed the series for a third season, which premiered on September 28, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2018/04/18/cbs-renewed-series-2018-hawaii-five-0-madam-secretary/|title=Hawaii Five-0, Madam Secretary and Bull Among CBS' 11 Latest Renewals|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|date=April 18, 2018|accessdate=April 18, 2018|work=[[TV Line]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/cbs-fall-premiere-dates-2018-big-bang-theory-survivor-1202423513/|title=CBS Fall 2018 Premiere Dates: 'Big Bang' & 'Young Sheldon' To Help Launch 'Magnum PI' & 'Murphy Brown' Revival|work=Deadline Hollywood|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=July 9, 2018|accessdate=July 14, 2018}}</ref> In May 2019, the series was renewed for a fourth season by CBS,<ref name=\"S4Renewal\"/> which premiered on February 7, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2019/05/15/cbs-fall-lineup-2019-young-sheldon/|title=CBS Fall Schedule: Sheldon Scores Big Perch, Criminal Minds Farewell Run and MacGyver Held for Midseason|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|website=TV Line|date=May 15, 2019|accessdate=May 15, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"S4Premiere\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/11/cbs-winter-schedule-midseason-criminal-minds-final-season-15-premiere-ncis-new-orleans-new-time-slot-survivor-season-40-undercover-boss-tommy-fbi-most-wanted-macgyver-premiere-date-1202782646/|title=CBS Sets Winter Schedule: 'Criminal Minds' Returns To Original Slot For Final Season, 'NCIS: New Orleans' Moves To Sunday|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=November 11, 2019|accessdate=November 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n[[MacGyver|Angus \"Mac\" MacGyver]] is an operative of a secret U.S. government organization where he uses his extraordinary talent for problem solving and his extensive knowledge of science to save lives.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cbs.com/shows/macgyver/about/ |title=About MacGyver |publisher=CBS}}</ref> \"With skills that are only limited by his creativity, Mac saves the day using paper clips instead of pistols, birthday candles instead of bombs, and gum instead of guns.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cbs.com/shows/macgyver/news/1005839/the-notorious-tools-of-macgyver-s-trade/ |title=The 7 Notorious Tools Of MacGyver's Trade |publisher=CBS}}</ref>\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{main|List of MacGyver characters}}\n\n===Main===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:4%;\" rowspan=\"2\" | Name\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:4%;\" rowspan=\"2\" | Portrayed by\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20%;\" colspan=\"4\" | Seasons\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:4%;\" | [[MacGyver (2016 TV series, season 1)|1]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:4%;\" | [[MacGyver (2016 TV series, season 2)|2]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:4%;\" | [[MacGyver (2016 TV series, season 3)|3]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:4%;\" | [[MacGyver (2016 TV series, season 4)|4]]\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[MacGyver|Angus MacGyver]]\n| [[Lucas Till]]\n| colspan=\"4\" {{cMain}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Jack Dalton (MacGyver)|Jack Dalton]]\n| [[George Eads]]\n| colspan=\"3\" {{cMain}}{{efn|Episodes 1\u201314 of season 3 only.}}\n| {{cNone}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Peter Thornton (MacGyver)#2016 Reboot|Patricia Thornton]]\n| [[Sandrine Holt]]\n| {{cMain}}{{efn|Episodes 1\u201312 of season 1 only.}}\n| colspan=\"3\" {{cNone}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Riley Davis\n| [[Tristin Mays]]\n| colspan=\"4\" {{cMain}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Wilt Bozer\n| [[Justin Hires]]\n| colspan=\"4\" {{cMain}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" |Matilda \"Matty\" Webber\n| [[Meredith Eaton]]\n| colspan=\"4\" {{cMain}}{{efn|Episodes 13\u201317 of season 1, recurring; episodes 18\u201321, main.}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | Samantha Cage\n| [[Isabel Lucas]]\n| {{cNone}}\n| {{cMain}}{{efn|Episodes 1\u201311, 13 of season 2 only.}}\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cNone}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Desiree \"Desi\" Nguyen}}\n| [[Levy Tran]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cNone}}\n| {{cRecurring}}\n| {{cMain}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Russell \"Russ/Rusty\" Taylor}}\n| [[Henry Ian Cusick]]\n| colspan=\"3\" {{cNone}}\n| {{cMain}}\n|}\n{{notelist}}\n\n* [[Lucas Till]] as [[MacGyver|Angus \"Mac\" MacGyver]]: A highly intelligent and incredibly resourceful U.S. operative who works for the Phoenix Foundation, a covert agency operating under the guise of a [[think tank]]. Trained as an [[Bomb disposal|EOD technician]] for the Army, Mac prefers to use non-lethal means to stop his enemies; he is never without his trusty [[Swiss Army knife]] and uses anything in his environment to his advantage. At the end of Season 2, Mac leaves the Phoenix due to his lack of trust in its leadership, but eventually returns when he realises how much his skillset is needed.\n* [[George Eads]] as [[List of MacGyver characters#Jack Dalton|Jack Dalton]] (seasons 1\u20133): Mac's partner in the field and a former [[Delta Force]] operator. Jack's history with Mac goes back to his days in the Army and unlike Mac, he is not afraid to use guns in the field. He also has history with Riley, because he was once in a relationship with her mother and had an altercation with her deadbeat father. While mostly easy-going and laid-back, Jack can get serious when the situation calls for it and often calls upon his special operations training to help the team get out of a tight spot. At the end of \"Father + Bride + Betrayal\", Jack leaves the Phoenix to track a terrorist thought to have been killed years earlier.\n* [[Sandrine Holt]] as [[Peter Thornton (MacGyver)#2016 Reboot|Patricia Thornton]] (season 1): Initial Director of Field Operations at the Phoenix Foundation and, in Mac's own words, the most successful clandestine operative in U.S. history. By the book and serious most of the time, Thornton regularly assigns the team their missions. In the 12th episode, \"Screwdriver\", she is discovered to be a mole working for the Organization and arrested.\n* [[Tristin Mays]] as [[List of MacGyver characters#New main characters in the 2016 reboot|Riley Davis]]: A tough-as-nails, sarcastic hacker who is hired by the Phoenix Foundation as their technical specialist. Riley was originally in prison for trying to hack the [[National Security Agency|NSA]] in order to save her mother from a reclusive hacktivist group. She had a strained relationship with Jack because he vanished from her and her mother's lives after an altercation with her abusive father, but now views Jack as a father figure.\n* [[Justin Hires]] as [[List of MacGyver characters#Wilt Bozer|Wilt Bozer]]: Mac's best friend whom he has known since childhood. He is initially a struggling film director possessing several artistic talents. His ability to create lifelike masks and facial prosthetics gets him hired at the Phoenix Foundation. Bozer is a source of comic relief and often helps Riley in exchange for earning the digits to her phone number. When Bozer trains to be an agent at the Operative Training Center, he falls for fellow recruit Leanne Martin.\n* [[Meredith Eaton]] as [[List of MacGyver characters#New main characters in the 2016 reboot|Matilda \"Matty\" Webber]] (season 1\u2013present<!--Do not remove this section, it is necessary to denote that she was not main from the beginning but episode counts are not allowed per [[MOS:TVCAST]]-->): Thornton's replacement as Director of Operations at Phoenix Foundation and Jack's ex-boss from the CIA. It's revealed in \"Scavengers + Hard Drive + Dragonfly\" that she is married, but has not worn a wedding ring since her husband went on a deep undercover assignment.\n* [[Isabel Lucas]] as [[List of MacGyver characters#New main characters in the 2016 reboot|Samantha Cage]] (season 2), CIA officer and formerly of [[Special Air Service Regiment|SASR]] 4th Squadron. After she is discharged from the CIA for her unsanctioned actions in the second season premiere, Matty recruits her into the Phoenix Foundation. In the episode \"Bullet + Pen\", she is ambushed and shot by the assassin Murdoc in her apartment, but survives, and returns home to her native Australia to recover.\n* [[Levy Tran]] as [[List of MacGyver characters#New recurring characters in the 2016 reboot|Desiree \"Desi\" Nguyen]] (season 4, recurring season 3), Desi is a new recruit for the Phoenix Foundation who takes over for Jack after he leaves. Though she does things differently than Jack, she seems to be equally effective. She is particularly skilled in martial arts. The season 4 premiere reveals that Desi and Mac had a brief romantic relationship that ended badly.\n* [[Henry Ian Cusick]] as Russell \"Russ/Rusty\" Taylor (season 4), Ex-MI6 Agent-Turned-Private Military Contractor described as a master manipulator and salesman, Russ is skilled in propaganda and lie detection, and boasts an extremely high emotional intelligence. He is also very wealthy, and thus is used to both getting his way and enjoying the spoils of war (including expensive suits, fast cars, private jets and a house in Monte Carlo).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2019/06/28/henry-ian-cusick-macgyver-season-4-series-regular/|title=Henry Ian Cusick Joins MacGyver Season 4 Cast as Master Manipulator|work=TVLine|last=Mitovich|first=Matt Webb|date=June 28, 2019|accessdate=June 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Recurring===\n* [[Tracy Spiridakos]] as [[List of MacGyver characters#Nikki Carpenter|Nikki Carpenter]]: An undercover CIA operative who formerly worked as a hacker for DXS until she faked her own death. She is also Mac's ex-girlfriend.\n* [[Amy Acker]] as [[List of MacGyver characters#New characters in the 2016 reboot|Sarah Adler]]: CIA operative and Jack's ex-girlfriend.\n* [[David Dastmalchian]] as [[Murdoc]]: A brilliant assassin, also known as Suspect 218, and a frequent opponent of Mac. He is at first thought to have been sent by Nikki, but is later revealed to have been sent by Thornton.\n* Kate Bond as Jill Morgan: A forensics expert at the Phoenix Foundation. The team members occasionally ask her for help on personal missions. She is seen leading a task force to help capture Murdoc in the third season premiere. Murdoc kills her at the end of the episode.\n* [[Lauren V\u00e9lez]] as Cassandra Glover, a coordinator for Operative Training Center.\n* [[Reign Edwards]] as Leanna Martin: A recruit at the Operative Training Center, Bozer meets and becomes good friends with Leanna, later leading to a romantic relationship that they try to keep secret. In the season 2 finale, Leanna is hired by the Phoenix Foundation.\n* [[William Baldwin]] as Elwood Davis, Riley's estranged father.\n* [[Lance Gross]] as Billy Colton, a member of the Colton bounty hunting family who becomes Riley's love interest.\n* [[Sheryl Lee Ralph]] as Mama Colton, Billy's mother and the head of the Colton bounty hunting family.\n* Emerson Brooks as Charlie Robinson, Mac's old war pal who is now a bomb squad specialist.\n* [[Tate Donovan]] as James MacGyver/\"Oversight\", Mac's father who had mysteriously disappeared from his life.\n* [[Sibongile Mlambo]] as Nasha, Mac's Nigerian girlfriend whom he met after briefly leaving the Phoenix Foundation.\n* [[Brendan Hines]] as Ethan Raines, Matty's husband who went deep undercover for eight years shortly after their marriage. It's revealed in season 3 that, to keep his cover, Ethan married another woman and has a young child with her.\n* [[Leonardo Nam]] as Aubrey, Riley's brief love interest (season 4)\n*[[Jeri Ryan]] as Gwendolyn \"Gwen\" Hayes, MacGyver's aunt (his mother\u2019s sister); an ex-DXS agent who was presumed dead; now head of CODEX.<ref>https://www.tvinsider.com/915824/macgyver-season-4-jeri-ryan-mac-aunt-gwendolyn-hayes/amp/</ref><ref>https://tvline.com/2020/02/20/macgyver-jeri-ryan-cast-aunt-gwendolyn-hayes-season-4/</ref>\n\n===Notable guests===\n* [[Daniel Dae Kim]] as [[List of Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series) characters#Chin Ho Kelly|Lieutenant Chin Ho Kelly]]: Crossover character from ''[[Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series)|Hawaii Five-0]]''. A member of the Five-0 Task Force\n* [[Grace Park (actress)|Grace Park]] as [[List of Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series) characters#Kono Kalakaua|Officer Kono Kalakaua]]: Crossover character from ''Hawaii Five-0''. A member of the Five-0 Task Force\n* [[Taylor Wily]] as [[Kamekona Tupuola]]: Crossover character from ''Hawaii Five-0''. An [[entrepreneur]] and confidential informant for the Five-0 Task Force\n* [[Michael Des Barres]] as Nicholas Helman, a hitman who is also Murdoc's mentor. (Des Barres played Murdoc in the original ''MacGyver'' series.)\n* [[Sarah Sokolovic]] as Amber, Murdoc's ex-wife and mother of their son, Cassian\n* [[Sean Cameron Michael]] as The Ghost Bomber\n* Presilah Nunez as ATF Agent Maria Ramirez, MacGyver's friend from their time in the Army and the handler of ATF K-9 Cody.\n* [[Peter Weller]] as Elliot Mason, a former military special ops officer who holds a grudge against James MacGyver\n*[[Jorge Garcia]] as [[List of Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series) characters#Jerry Ortega|Jerry Ortega]], Crossover character from ''Hawaii Five-0''. A former member of the Five-0 Task Force<ref>https://cartermatt.com/394753/macgyver-season-4-spoilers-jorge-garcia-making-hawaii-five-0-crossover/amp/</ref>\n* [[Brian \"Q\" Quinn]]\n* [[James \"Murr\" Murray]]\n* [[Salvatore \"Sal\" Vulcano]]\n* [[Joe Gatto (comedian)|Joseph \"Joe\" Gatto]]\n*[[Scottie Thompson]] as Ellen, Angus\u2019 Mom\n* John Ales as Nikola Tesla\n*Mark Boyd as Alexander Graham Bell\n*Tom Thon as Thomas Edison\n*Cuyle Carvin as DXS Agent Charles\n\n==Production==\n\n===Development===\n[[File:MacGyver_(2016)_Season_1_Title_Card.jpg|thumb|right|225px|Title card for the first season, done in the style of the original series. Subsequent seasons featured a different title card after the opening sequence was redesigned.]]\nIn October 2015, the original series' executive producer, [[Henry Winkler]], signed on to produce a remake series with [[James Wan]] and [[R. Scott Gemmill]] for [[CBS]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/09/macgyver-series-remake-cbs-james-wan-henry-winkler-1201566340/|title='MacGyver' Series Remake Set At CBS, James Wan & Henry Winkler Producing|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=October 2, 2016|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=August 5, 2016}}</ref> which owns the rights to ''MacGyver'' through its acquisition of the original [[Paramount Television]].  In February 2016, it was announced that CBS had greenlit production of a pilot episode written by [[Paul Downs Colaizzo]] and directed by Wan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/02/macgyver-reboot-dr-phil-drama-bull-cbs-pilot-1201695415/|title='MacGyver' Reboot, Dr. Phil Drama 'Bull' Get CBS Pilot Orders|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=February 2, 2016|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref> Wan pulled out from directing due to scheduling conflicts and was replaced by [[David Von Ancken]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://deadline.com/2016/05/macgyver-series-cbs-changes-peter-lenkov-1201755899/|title='MacGyver': What We Know About The Changes On Newly Picked Up CBS Series|date=May 14, 2016|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|accessdate=July 30, 2016|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2016, the network picked up the series. Co-creator and executive producer [[Peter M. Lenkov]] will serve as the [[showrunner]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/05/training-day-bull-macgyver-the-great-indoors-matt-leblanc-jason-katims-cbs-series-1201755376/|title='Training Day', 'Bull', 'MacGyver', 'The Great Indoors', Matt LeBlanc Comedy & Jason Katims Drama Picked Up By CBS|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=May 13, 2016|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref>  On May 18, 2016, CBS released a first video trailer for new series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2pS39X658Vw|title=MacGyver First Look|date=May 18, 2016|publisher=CBS}}</ref> In June 2016, the network scrapped the original pilot, with Wan to direct a new pilot episode.<ref name=\"new_pilot\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/james-wan-direct-cbs-rebooted-903740|title=James Wan to Direct CBS' Rebooted 'MacGyver' Pilot|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|date=June 16, 2016|work=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref>\n\nOn October 17, 2016, CBS ordered a full season of 21 episodes.<ref name=\"Bull, Kevin & MacGyver\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/bull-kevin-can-wait-macgyver-938813|title='Bull,' 'Kevin Can Wait' and 'MacGyver' Grab Full-Season Pickups at CBS|last=Stanhope|first=Kate|work=Hollywood Reporter|date=October 17, 2016|accessdate=October 17, 2016}}</ref> On March 23, 2017, CBS renewed the series for a second season, which premiered on September 29, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/03/cbs-early-renewals-macgyver-superior-donuts-life-in-pieces-hawaii-five-0-blue-bloods-1202049276/|title=CBS Renews 5 Freshman & 11 Returning Series, Including 'MacGyver', 'Superior Donuts', 'Life In Pieces' & 'Hawaii Five-0'|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=March 23, 2017|accessdate=March 23, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/06/cbs-fall-2017-premiere-dates-young-sheldon-seal-team-9jkl-1202105923/|title=CBS Sets Fall 2017 Premiere Dates For 'Young Sheldon', '9 JKL' & Returning Series|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|work=Deadline Hollywood|date=June 1, 2017|accessdate=June 1, 2017}}</ref> On May 9, 2019, it was announced that CBS renewed the series for a fourth season,<ref name=\"S4Renewal\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/macgyver-renewed-season-4-cbs-1202605487/|title='MacGyver' Renewed For Season 4 By CBS|work=Deadline Hollywood|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|last2=Petski|first2=Denise|date=May 9, 2019|accessdate=May 9, 2019}}</ref> which premiered on February 7, 2020.<ref name=\"S4Premiere\"/> On November 6, 2019, it was announced that CBS had ordered an additional nine episodes in this fourth season.<ref>{{cite web|title=MacGyver - Season 4 - CBS Orders Additional Episodes|url=https://www.spoilertv.com/2019/11/macgyver-season-4-cbs-orders-additional.html|website=SpoilerTV|accessdate=November 6, 2019|date=November 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nIn March 2016, [[Lucas Till]] was announced as the new MacGyver, Joshua Boone as Gunner, MacGyver's best friend from high school, alongside with former and longtime ''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation|CSI]]'' star [[George Eads]] as [[List of MacGyver characters|Jack Dalton]], who was originally named Lincoln, a man who could easily be written off as an eccentric conspiracy theorist but is a legitimate government employee with great capability for compassion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/03/lucas-till-cast-macgyver-cbs-pilot-x-men-1201723767/|title='X-Men's Lucas Till To Play MacGyver In CBS Reboot Pilot|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=March 21, 2016|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref> Later cast were [[Addison Timlin]] as Mickey, an app developer who is aggressively progressive in her political views but who has a soft spot for MacGyver, and [[Michelle Krusiec]] as Agent Croix, Dalton's sister who works for the Department of Homeland Security.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/03/macgyver-addison-timlin-michelle-krusiec-cast-cbs-pilot-1201727527/|title='MacGyver': Addison Timlin & Michelle Krusiec Cast In CBS Pilot|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=March 28, 2016|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref> However, the original pilot with this casting was scrapped by CBS in June 2016 \u2013 a new pilot episode was ordered with only Till and Eads from the original cast continuing on to the revised version of the show.<ref name=\"new_pilot\" />\n\nAround the same time the new pilot was ordered, [[Justin Hires]] was cast as Wilt Bozer, MacGyver's roommate who is an aspiring filmmaker.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/06/macgyver-rush-hour-justin-hires-cast-cbs-series-reboot-1201771878/|title='MacGyver': 'Rush Hour's Justin Hires Cast In CBS Series Reboot|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=June 13, 2016|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref> In July 2016, ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' reported that [[Sandrine Holt]] had been cast as Patricia Thornton, an ex-field agent who was the director of operations for the Department of External Services,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/macgyver-casts-sandrine-holt-as-series-regular-1201815294/|title='MacGyver' Casts Sandrine Holt as Series Regular|last=Prudom|first=Laura|date=July 15, 2016|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref> and that [[Tristin Mays]] was cast as Riley Davis, a highly unpredictable computer hacker with a chip on her shoulder.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/macgyver-tristan-mays-cast-cbs-1201824668/|title=Tristin Mays Joins 'MacGyver' Completing Cast of CBS Reboot|last=Wagmeister|first=Elizabeth|date=July 27, 2016|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref>\n\nOn November 26, 2018, it was announced that George Eads was set to depart the series midway through the show's third season. According to creator [[Peter M. Lenkov]], Eads had asked to be released from his contract for some time so he could spend more time with his young daughter who resides in Los Angeles; the series is filmed in Atlanta. Producers ultimately agreed with Eads being written out of the show but left the opportunity for him to return as a guest star in the future. His final episode aired on February 1, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/macgyver-star-george-eads-exit-1163956|title='MacGyver' Star George Eads to Exit|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|publisher=The Hollywood Reporter|date=November 26, 2018|accessdate=November 27, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://popculture.com/tv-shows/2019/02/02/macgyver-says-goodbye-george-eads-emotional-episode/ |title='MacGyver' Says Goodbye to George Eads in Emotional Episode |website=popculture.com |access-date=February 2, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Episodes ==\n{{main|List of MacGyver (2016 TV series) episodes}}\n{{:List of MacGyver (2016 TV series) episodes}}\n\n===Crossovers===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\" width=\"100%\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" width=\"22%\"|Crossover between !! rowspan=\"2\"|Episode(s) !! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"10%\"|Type !! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"30%\"|Actors crossing over !! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"10%\"|Date aired\n|-\n! width=\"11%\"|Series A !! width=\"11%\"|Series B\n|-\n| style=\"background:#FFFF00;\" | ''[[MacGyver (2016 TV series)|MacGyver]]'' || style=\"background:#6495ED;\" | ''[[Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series)|Hawaii Five-0]]'' || \"[[MacGyver (2016 TV series, season 1)#ep18|Flashlight]]\"<br /><small>(''MacGyver'' 1.18)</small>  || One-part crossover || '''Appearing in Series A:''' [[Daniel Dae Kim]], [[Grace Park (actress)|Grace Park]], [[Taylor Wily]] || {{startdate|2017|3|10}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{main|Flashlight (MacGyver)}}\nThe [[Organizations in MacGyver#Phoenix Foundation|Phoenix Foundation]] team of ''[[MacGyver (2016 TV series)|MacGyver]]'' gets rerouted to Hawaii after a 7.2 magnitude earthquake hits the coast of Hawaii. While aiding Detective Chin Ho Kelly and Officer [[List of Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series) characters#Kono Kalakaua|Kono Kalakaua]] from Five-0 task force, they also have to deal with Chinese intelligence soldiers who use the earthquake to steal top-secret weaponry that the scientists are currently developing.\n|-\n| style=\"background:#FFFF00;\" | ''[[MacGyver (2016 TV series)|MacGyver]]'' || style=\"background:#6495ED;\" | ''Hawaii Five-0'' || Unknown [[MacGyver (2016 TV series, season 4)|fourth season]] episode<!--<br /><small>(''MacGyver'' 4.?)</small>-->  || Guest appearance || '''Appearing in Series A:''' [[Jorge Garcia]] || {{startdate|2020}}\n|-\n<!--| colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:left;\" |-->\n|}\n\n==International broadcast==\nIn the United Kingdom, [[Sky UK|Sky]] acquired the rights to ''MacGyver'', and the series commenced airing on [[Sky1]] from February 8, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/01/sky-takes-macgyver-reboot-americas-next-top-model-for-uk-tyra-banks-cbs-rita-ora-1201893781/|title=Sky Acquires 'MacGyver' Reboot & 'America's Next Top Model' For UK|first=Diana|last=Lodderhose|date=25 January 2017|publisher=}}</ref> [[Fox Crime]] Turkey broadcasts serials a week after original run.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxchannels.com.tr/diziler/foxcrime/macgyver|title=FOXCRIME - MacGyver|first=Fox|last=TV|website=www.foxchannels.com.tr}}</ref> Veronica broadcasts the episodes in the Netherlands, a few weeks after US broadcast.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.veronicatv.nl/programmas/macgyver/|title=MacGyver|publisher=}}</ref> In Australia, the series airs on the [[Network Ten|Ten]] network.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tenplay.com.au/channel-ten/macgyver |title=Watch MacGyver \u2013 Channel TEN \u2013 Network Ten |website=tenplay |publisher=[[Network Ten]] |access-date=2 April 2017}}</ref> The show also airs in [[Asia]] on [[AXN Asia|AXN]]. The series premiered in Latin America on [[Universal Channel]] on October 26, 2017.\nIn Germany the series premiered in June 2017 on [[Sat.1]]. The series premiered in France on [[M6 (TV channel)]] on January 5, 2018. In Italy, the series airs on [[RAI 2]]. In South Africa it airs on pay-TV channel [[M-Net City]], as well as on free-to-air channels, [[e.tv]] and [[eExtra]].\n\n==Reception==\n===Ratings===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Season\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Time slot ([[Eastern Time Zone (North America)|ET]]/[[Pacific Time Zone|PT]])\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Episodes\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\" | Season premiere\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\" | Season finale\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | TV season\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Rank\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#ffdead;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Viewers<br />(in millions)\n|-\n! Date\n! span style=\"width:7%; font-size:smaller; line-height:100%;\"| Viewers<br />(in millions)\n! Date\n! span style=\"width:10%; font-size:smaller; line-height:100%;\"| Viewers<br />(in millions)\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 1\n| rowspan=\"4\" | Friday 8:00&nbsp;pm\n| 21\n| style=\"font-size:11px;\"| September 23, 2016\n| 10.90<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/09/26/friday-final-ratings-sept-23-2016/ |title=Friday final ratings: 'Hawaii Five-0' adjusts up, 'MacGyver' and 'Exorcist' hold |last=Porter |first=Rick |work=TV by the Numbers |date=September 26, 2016 |accessdate=September 26, 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160927134015/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/09/26/friday-final-ratings-sept-23-2016/ |archivedate=September 27, 2016 }}</ref>\n| style=\"font-size:11px;\"| April 14, 2017\n| 6.57<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/friday-final-ratings-april-14-2017/|title='Shark Tank' adjusts up, 'The Originals' adjusts down: Friday final ratings